inputs.description: A collection of arguments for invoking getMultiRegionAccessPoint.

accountId.description: The AWS account ID of the S3 Multi-Region Access Point. Defaults to automatically determined account ID of the AWS provider.

name.description: The name of the Multi-Region Access Point.

outputs.description: A collection of values returned by getMultiRegionAccessPoint.

alias.description: The alias for the Multi-Region Access Point.

arn.description: Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Multi-Region Access Point.

createdAt.description: Timestamp when the resource has been created.

domainName.description: The DNS domain name of the S3 Multi-Region Access Point in the format _`alias`_.accesspoint.s3-global.amazonaws.com. For more information, see the documentation on [Multi-Region Access Point Requests](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/userguide/MultiRegionAccessPointRequests.html).

id.description: The provider-assigned unique ID for this managed resource.

publicAccessBlocks.description: Public Access Block of the Multi-Region Access Point. Detailed below.

regions.description: A collection of the regions and buckets associated with the Multi-Region Access Point.

status.description: The current status of the Multi-Region Access Point.
